Have another bite, my lord.

279
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:16,080
No.

280
00:12:16,280 --> 00:12:17,760
Just try it.

281
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:21,520
I said no. Take it away.

282
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:28,020
(Xianquan Tavern)

283
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:33,680
(What kind of garbage)

284
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:34,720
(is Xianquan Tavern making?)

285
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:36,280
(It's so disgusting!)

286
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:42,000
Mr. Li, there's trouble.

287
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,320
Someone's causing a scene downstairs.

288
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:44,480
Causing a scene?

289
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:45,840
Let's go

290
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:46,760
check it out.

291
00:12:52,400 --> 00:12:55,080
Does Xianquan Tavern
even know how to cook?

292
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:57,880
If you can't cook,
then just close up shop!

293
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:03,600
What's wrong with that guy's taste buds?

294
00:13:03,920 --> 00:13:05,880
The chefs at Xianquan Tavern

295
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:07,880
are the absolute best
in all of Feng City.

296
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:08,960
No doubt about it.

297
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:10,520
Especially those new dishes
they've rolled out

298
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:12,080
these past few days.

299
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:12,720
They're so delicious

300
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:14,400
that I've bitten my tongue
more times than I can count.

301
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:24,120
(Coming alone to stir up trouble?)

302
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:26,240
(This guy isn't brave.)

303
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,280
(He's just brainless.)

304
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,400
Alright, go on back to work.

305
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:35,120
Sir,

306
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,880
I'm Li Yunhe, the owner

307
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:37,760
of Xianquan Tavern.

308
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:39,240
May I ask what exactly

309
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:41,080
about this food
is not to your satisfaction?

310
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:44,120
So you're Li Yunhe,
the Zhou live-in son-in-law.

311
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,000
This food of yours?

312
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:47,760
I don't like it.

313
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:49,640
Let's run!

314
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:55,880
So?

315
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:57,680
Sir, what exactly

316
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,400
is your point?

317
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:03,200
Shut this dump of a tavern down.

318
00:14:03,680 --> 00:14:05,080
And what if I don't?

319
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:11,080
Hey,

320
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:12,760
tell your boss not to be so stubborn.

321
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,120
That man is bad news.

322
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:15,680
That guy is Long Er,

323
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:17,560
known far and wide for his fighting.

324
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:19,360
If your boss has a conflict with him,

325
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:21,240
your tavern will come out
on the losing end.

326
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,360
Long Er

327
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:24,360
has long since thrown in his lot
with the Marquis House.

328
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:26,560
You people at Xianquan Tavern
can't afford to cross him.

329
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,480
Just pay him off and be done with it.

330
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:29,840
Better to settle things quietly.

331
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:42,120
So

332
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,640
you're Mr. Long.

333
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:45,760
I've heard so much about you.

334
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:47,240
Hey,

335
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:50,480
since you know my fearsome reputation,

336
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,640
if you don't
close this place down right now,

337
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:54,440
you're itching for a beating.

338
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:55,240
Mr. Long,

339
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:57,240
let me make this crystal clear upfront.

340
00:14:57,680 --> 00:14:58,720
If you've come to my tavern

341
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:00,040
looking for trouble,

342
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:02,080
I'm afraid
you've picked the wrong place.

343
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,520
Well, I've picked it.

344
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:06,240
Got a problem with it?

345
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:07,840
If you've got the guts,
come with me to the arena

346
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:08,960
and fight it out.

347
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,240
So this was all

348
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:13,160
to get me into the arena.

349
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:14,640
Cut the chatter.

350
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:15,600
You in or not?

351
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:17,280
Seems the Marquis House
has run out of new tricks.

352
00:15:17,280 --> 00:15:18,360
Just these same few moves

353
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:19,720
over and over.

354
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:22,640
Fine, I'll get in the arena with you.

355
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:23,840
But

356
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:25,840
we've got to have some kind
of stakes, don't we?

357
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:28,840
If you manage to win,

358
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:31,760
I will be your slave,
your beast of burden.

359
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:34,520
Through fire and flood,
I'll follow your every command.

360
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:37,080
But if you lose...

361
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:38,240
What happens

362
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,640
if I lose?

363
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:41,440
Mr. Lu Said

364
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:44,440
as long as you're still breathing,
you're just in the way.

365
00:15:44,920 --> 00:15:46,040
Best if you were dead.

366
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:22,100
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

367
00:16:22,260 --> 00:16:25,460
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

368
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:28,700
♪Who took the March rain♪

369
00:16:28,940 --> 00:16:32,300
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

370
00:16:32,660 --> 00:16:35,460
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

371
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:38,820
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

372
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:45,620
♪Needle and thread
stitch away the marks of time♪

373
00:16:45,660 --> 00:16:49,100
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

374
00:16:49,340 --> 00:16:52,180
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

375
00:16:52,340 --> 00:16:54,620
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

376
00:16:54,620 --> 00:16:58,820
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

377
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:02,180
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

378
00:17:02,340 --> 00:17:05,460
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

379
00:17:05,980 --> 00:17:08,900
♪In this life I'd be a cloud-tailor♪

380
00:17:09,060 --> 00:17:15,580
♪Never failing the stars,
nor failing you♪

381
00:17:41,860 --> 00:17:45,380
♪Fine rain falls outside the pavilion♪

382
00:17:45,620 --> 00:17:48,780
♪With honors won, an old friend returns♪

383
00:17:49,380 --> 00:17:52,100
♪Who took the March rain♪

384
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:55,620
♪To dye the silk against the skin♪

385
00:17:56,020 --> 00:17:58,900
♪Yam juice enriches the silk threads♪

386
00:17:58,980 --> 00:18:02,700
♪Weaving the Milky Way
down to the mortal world♪

387
00:18:02,740 --> 00:18:06,020
♪Warp and weft entwine,
one shuttle, one dream♪

388
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:08,980
♪As seasons change♪

389
00:18:08,980 --> 00:18:12,620
♪Cutting a yard of the misty rain♪

390
00:18:12,620 --> 00:18:15,460
♪Embroidering half a scroll
of earthly verses♪

391
00:18:15,540 --> 00:18:18,100
♪Where the golden honors hang high♪

392
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:22,180
♪The clouds dance in the air♪

393
00:18:22,180 --> 00:18:25,500
♪Brewing wine, we speak of legends♪

394
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:29,220
♪In fine liquor,
true feelings are revealed♪

395
00:18:29,620 --> 00:18:32,740
♪Washing away
a lifetime of wear and tear♪

396
00:18:32,740 --> 00:18:35,620
♪Only for you♪

397
00:18:35,620 --> 00:18:39,220
♪On the street of golden honors,
the music rises♪

398
00:18:39,340 --> 00:18:42,100
♪The moon moves west
beyond the pavilion♪

399
00:18:42,220 --> 00:18:44,780
♪Wine runs dry, yet the revelry lingers♪

400
00:18:44,780 --> 00:18:48,860
♪In silk, I seek a kindred soul♪

401
00:18:48,860 --> 00:18:52,180
♪The rain has ceased,
clouds begin to clear♪

402
00:18:52,220 --> 00:18:55,580
♪The fragrant silk billows
under the low-hung stars♪

403
00:18:56,420 --> 00:19:02,100
♪I'd cut the clouds and morning glow
to drape over you♪

404
00:19:03,180 --> 00:19:07,300
♪A single bolt of silk becomes♪

405
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:13,100
♪Your wedding gown♪
